         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="saint-44" ana="#syriaca-saint">
               <persName xml:id="name44-2" xml:lang="en">Philoxenus of Mabbug</persName>
               <persName xml:id="name44-3" xml:lang="fr-x-fiey" source="#bib44-1">PHILOXÈNE</persName>
               <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/person/44</idno>
               <idno type="FIEY">347</idno>
               <sex value="M" source="#bib44-1">male</sex>
               <death when="0523" syriaca-computed-start="0523-01-01" source="#bib44-1">0523</death>
               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib44-1">Barsaum, Lu'lu '2 , 281-89.
Honigmann, Eveques et eveches, 66- 68.
Trad. anglaise de Ia Vie par A. Mingana, dans The Expositor 8:19 (1920), 149- 60.
Ses canons : Voobus, Sammlungen, 316, 493.
A. De Halleux, "A Ia source d'une biographie expurgee de Philoxene de Mabboug" ,
OLP 6- 7 (1975- 76) , 253-66.</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">Philoxenus was a Bishop of Mabbug. He was born in Beth Garmai and frequented the schools of Edessa, Telʿada, and Qartmin. He was made Bishop of Mabbug and fought against the Nestorians and Flavian. After the ascent of Justin I, Philoxenus was exiled and imprisoned in the kitchen of a hostel in Paphlagonia.</note>
               <bibl xml:id="bib44-1">
                  <title level="m" xml:lang="fr">Saints Syriaques</title>
                  <title level="a" xml:lang="fr">PHILOXÈNE</title>
                  <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/650"/>
                  <citedRange unit="entry">347</citedRange>
               </bibl>
               <bibl xml:id="bib44-3">
                  <author>Barsaum</author>
                  <title>Lu'lu '2</title>
                  <citedRange>281-89.</citedRange>
               </bibl>
